neighborhood_overview: There are Michelin-rated restaurants in the area, trendy bars and cafes, a Key Foods supermarket (as well as a farmer's market grocery), and a CVS. As the area is historically Greek, there are also wonderful Greek restaurants. In the summertime, Astoria park is a beautiful place for a picnic overlooking the river, with a view of Manhattan on the other side.
transit: Astoria is a safe and quaint neighborhood, and our apartment is located only 2 blocks from a train line that gets you to midtown Manhattan in 20 minutes. It's a perfect respite from the crowds, while still closer to Central Park, major museums, and popular attractions than many tri-borough locations!
